         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">July 3rd 1885 ¶ 17 Woodlane ¶ Falmouth. ¶ Dear Sir ¶  ¶ I have received a letter from Baron von Mueller ¶  together with a leaf of the Litsea at first supposed to be an oak, which he asks me to forwar...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">M85.07.03</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Henry Guppy to William Thiselton-Dyer</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG, Kew, Herbarium, with specimen of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Litsea">Litsea</name> guppyi</seg>, K000815308</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">July 3rd 1885</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">17 Woodlane</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Falmouth.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have received a letter from Baron von Mueller<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found.</p>
               </note> together with a leaf of the <name key="Litsea">Litsea</name> at first supposed to be an oak, which he asks me to forward to Sir Joseph Hooker and yourself.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I was unwittingly the cause of the misconception by informing Baron Mueller that this tree had true acorns: and as I have received so much kindness at his hands, I am anxious that in making the correction, reference should be made to my having wrongly described the fruit to him.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">The herbarium sheet is heavily annotated including a note</seg> [<seg style="font-style: italic; ">by Daniel Oliver?]</seg>:<seg style="font-style: italic; "> </seg>Described as a <seg style="">
                        <hi rend="underline">Quercus</hi>
                     </seg> by F v Mueller, (Vic. Nat. dec/84) <seg style="font-style: italic; ">[i.e. B84.12.03, pp. 123-4]</seg> Mr Guppy having given him leaves only as of an Acorn-bearing tree.</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See also M to J. Hooker, 10 December 1884, n. 5; M to J. Hooker, 6 January 1885, n. 4; and M to A. de Candolle, 28 April 1885.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>My list of Ferns from the British Museum has not yet arrived, but I am now going to enquire about it, as I expected it some time since.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">I am</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Yours faithfully</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>H B Guppy</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Litsea">Litsea</name>
            </p>
